WEBVTT

00:01.569 --> 00:03.304
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Ah, friends.

00:03.337 --> 00:04.472
The times, they are a-changing.
First, our Jane.

00:04.505 --> 00:06.174
She was recently dumped.

00:06.207 --> 00:08.442
Plus her book got
mediocre reviews.

00:08.476 --> 00:12.613
And then this happened.
I know! OMG, right?

00:12.646 --> 00:14.048
Another OMG?

00:14.082 --> 00:16.250
Alba said no
to Jorge's proposal.

00:16.284 --> 00:17.551
Oh, and did I mention

00:17.585 --> 00:20.488
Rafael was living
with the Villanuevas now?

00:20.521 --> 00:22.790
See, his sister Luisa
took all his money,

00:22.823 --> 00:25.159
which meant Mateo had to say
good-bye to private school.

00:25.193 --> 00:27.161
Unfortunately,
Jane's local school district

00:27.195 --> 00:28.262
wasn't so great.

00:28.296 --> 00:29.397
But...

00:29.430 --> 00:30.598
Did you know

00:30.631 --> 00:31.965
that your parents live in
the Elbamare School District?

00:31.999 --> 00:35.203
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR: So, yeah,
they decided to send him there.

00:35.236 --> 00:36.104
On the down low.

00:36.137 --> 00:38.072
Also facing
child care challenges,

00:38.106 --> 00:40.774
Jane's father Rogelio.

00:40.808 --> 00:42.543
See, he was married to Xo,

00:42.576 --> 00:43.611
but had a baby with Darci.

00:43.644 --> 00:45.513
Oh, and did I mention,

00:45.546 --> 00:48.482
Darci was dating his archrival
and co

00:48.516 --> 00:50.684
I know! Straight out of
a telenovela, right?

00:50.718 --> 00:52.320
But imagine this.

00:52.353 --> 00:53.721
Petra's twin sister Anezka

00:53.754 --> 00:55.789
convinced Rafael's sister Luisa

00:55.823 --> 00:58.792
that she was hallucinating
some guy named Carl.

00:58.826 --> 01:01.562
So, Luisa checked herself
into a mental institution.

01:01.595 --> 01:04.565
But here's the thing, friends,
Carl was real.

01:04.598 --> 01:08.236
And to add to the crazy,
Anezka started spiraling.

01:08.269 --> 01:10.804
So she faked her own death
to see who really loved her.

01:10.838 --> 01:12.473
And she briefly thought
she could trust Petra.

01:12.506 --> 01:14.275
Until she realized
she couldn't.

01:14.308 --> 01:16.444
And then this happened.

01:16.477 --> 01:19.147
Which, my friends,
is where we left off.

01:20.514 --> 01:24.418
When Jane Gloriana Villanueva
was ten years old,

01:24.452 --> 01:27.521
the day she had dreamed about
finally came.

01:29.690 --> 01:34.495
The very first kiss
between Teresa and Ramiro

01:34.528 --> 01:35.596
on Las Rutas de Pasión.

01:35.629 --> 01:38.332
JANE: How do they know which way
to move their heads?

01:38.366 --> 01:40.601
Uh, well, they probably
just rehearsed.

01:40.634 --> 01:43.571
No, I mean in real life.

01:43.604 --> 01:46.474
How am I gonna know what to do?

02:01.555 --> 02:03.491
Okay, here's the real deal.

02:03.524 --> 02:06.194
It won't be anything
like Las Rutas de Pasión,

02:06.227 --> 02:07.395
so set your expectations low.

02:07.428 --> 02:09.363
The clouds
aren't gonna part,

02:09.397 --> 02:10.531
angels won't sing,

02:10.564 --> 02:11.932
it'll probably be
a little awkward.

02:11.965 --> 02:15.536
So, what happens?
What do you do?

02:15.569 --> 02:17.205
Well, you just open
your mouth a little,

02:17.238 --> 02:20.374
and your tongue will touch his--
or hers, either way.

02:20.408 --> 02:22.376
My tongue?

02:22.410 --> 02:23.244
Yup.

02:23.277 --> 02:26.414
Do I just leave it there?
You move it,

02:26.447 --> 02:27.281
b-but not too much.

02:27.315 --> 02:29.950
How will I know
if I'm doing a good job?

02:29.983 --> 02:32.553
Trust me, you'll know.

02:32.586 --> 02:36.156
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Which brings us here. Now.

02:42.596 --> 02:44.298
What... was...

02:44.332 --> 02:45.899
I wasn't planning it,
I-I-I just...

02:45.933 --> 02:47.601
MATEO:
Mommy?

02:47.635 --> 02:49.770
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Oh, no, did he see?

02:49.803 --> 02:51.505
I'm scared to go
to kindergarten.

02:54.442 --> 02:55.476
Oh, sweetheart.

02:55.509 --> 02:56.944
Oh, my-- ah.

02:56.977 --> 02:58.579
It's gonna be
so much fun.

02:58.612 --> 03:00.548
But I don't have any friends.

03:00.581 --> 03:01.582
You'll meet some kids

03:01.615 --> 03:04.485
when we go to registration
tomorrow. Now, come on.

03:04.518 --> 03:05.519
You need some sleep.

03:05.553 --> 03:07.988
Mommy will lie
with you. Hmm?

03:13.361 --> 03:15.729
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR :
Well, he sure looks happy.

03:17.465 --> 03:20.401
And she looks...

03:20.434 --> 03:21.669
She looks...

03:25.706 --> 03:27.575
I'm sorry, friends,

03:27.608 --> 03:30.878
but I actually don't know
what the hell she's thinking.

03:47.395 --> 03:48.596
Back to reality.

03:49.630 --> 03:51.031
Hi, Petra.

03:51.064 --> 03:53.033
Hey, wait, wait, wait.
Slow down.

03:53.066 --> 03:54.635
I know your sister's dead.

03:54.668 --> 03:56.537
No, she wasn't
really dead before.

03:56.570 --> 03:57.638
That-- she faked her death

03:57.671 --> 03:59.707
because she was trying
to figure out who loved her.

03:59.740 --> 04:01.742
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR: Reality,
of course, being relative.

04:01.775 --> 04:02.743
So she's alive?

04:02.776 --> 04:03.877
No.

04:03.911 --> 04:06.847
I found out, she attacked me,
so I defended myself,

04:06.880 --> 04:08.582
and she fell off the balcony.

04:08.616 --> 04:10.518
So now she's actually dead.

04:10.551 --> 04:12.286
Oh, my God. That's...

04:12.320 --> 04:13.754
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Straight out of a telenovela!

04:13.787 --> 04:14.722
Self-defense.

04:14.755 --> 04:16.757
So, listen, I need you
to watch the girls.

04:16.790 --> 04:18.459
The nanny can't stay overnight,

04:18.492 --> 04:19.460
I'm stuck
at the police station.

04:19.493 --> 04:20.461
I'm going now.

04:20.494 --> 04:21.529
Are you okay?

04:21.562 --> 04:23.664
Do you have a lawyer?

04:23.697 --> 04:24.865
No, I don't need one.

04:24.898 --> 04:26.500
Like I said,
it was self-defense.

04:26.534 --> 04:29.537
Yeah, I knew a lot of guys
in prison who said that, too.

04:29.570 --> 04:31.339
Just get a lawyer, a good one.

04:31.372 --> 04:32.540
I have to go.

04:32.573 --> 04:35.676
That's my other line.
We'll talk later.

04:35.709 --> 04:37.345
What the hell
took so long, Krishna?

04:37.378 --> 04:39.947
Well, it's a long drive,
and I had to stop for gas,

04:39.980 --> 04:41.582
and then my debit card wasn't...
Stop.

04:41.615 --> 04:42.583
I don't actually care.

04:42.616 --> 04:43.551
Are you at the mental hospital?

04:43.584 --> 04:45.786
They prefer you call it
a "wellness center."

04:45.819 --> 04:46.720
Krishna!

04:46.754 --> 04:50.824
Sorry. Yes.
I'm here, but Luisa's gone.

04:50.858 --> 04:51.859
What?

04:51.892 --> 04:52.760
She checked herself out,

04:52.793 --> 04:53.694
and she didn't leave
any contact info.

04:53.727 --> 04:56.597
Oh, no.
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR: Uh-oh.

04:56.630 --> 04:58.666
Once I tell Luisa
that you and mother gaslit her,

04:58.699 --> 05:01.034
she's going to get out and sign
all her shares over to Rafael.

05:01.068 --> 05:02.870
I told her you and Rafael

05:02.903 --> 05:04.938
were the ones
who had been sending Carl

05:04.972 --> 05:06.440
and lighting her gas.

05:06.474 --> 05:07.240
And she seemed

05:07.274 --> 05:10.878
very, very angry
with her brother.

05:10.911 --> 05:13.581
Listen to me, get a P.I., okay?

05:13.614 --> 05:15.483
We need to find Luisa.

05:15.516 --> 05:19.553
Oh, and-and, oh,
get me a lawyer, a good one.

05:21.789 --> 05:23.357
DARCI:
What's wrong?

05:23.391 --> 05:25.593
What's wrong is that this
is my time with Baby,

05:25.626 --> 05:26.927
and you're sitting here...
milking.

05:26.960 --> 05:27.795
Pumping.

05:27.828 --> 05:30.063
And unfortunately,
you fed her early

05:30.097 --> 05:31.599
and got her off
her schedule.

05:31.632 --> 05:33.901
So if I don't pump,
these babies will blow.

05:33.934 --> 05:37.371
ESTEBAN:
Darci produces so much milk.

05:37.405 --> 05:39.907
She's overflowing.

05:39.940 --> 05:43.644
Like a goddess of... milk.

05:43.677 --> 05:44.912
DARCI:
Well, this goddess

05:44.945 --> 05:46.814
doesn't need another
clogged duct.

05:46.847 --> 05:49.016
Okay, get this
in the fridge,

05:49.049 --> 05:50.017
it's liquid gold.

05:50.050 --> 05:51.552
Come on, Moosh,
let's go.

05:51.585 --> 05:52.686
:
Ask her.

05:52.720 --> 05:53.821
ROGELIO:
Darci.

05:53.854 --> 05:54.822
I was thinking,

05:54.855 --> 05:57.625
maybe Baby could stay overnight
this weekend?

05:57.658 --> 05:59.527
Overnight? No way.

05:59.560 --> 06:01.094
Overnights don't happen
until she's a year old,

06:01.128 --> 06:03.631
per our contract.

06:03.664 --> 06:04.898
Now, give Baby to Esteban.

06:13.641 --> 06:16.477
See you on set, Rogelio.

06:19.647 --> 06:21.782
Bright side?
Our really difficult

06:21.815 --> 06:24.652
new family dynamic is something
we can talk about in therapy.

06:24.685 --> 06:26.086
I don't need to talk about that
with a therapist.

06:26.119 --> 06:27.555
I just need Esteban

06:27.588 --> 06:30.791
to get a D-list,
straight-to-Crackle film

06:30.824 --> 06:32.059
that shoots in Guadalajara.

06:33.694 --> 06:34.628
But like I said,

06:34.662 --> 06:36.664
I'll be happy
to accompany you to therapy

06:36.697 --> 06:38.632
to help you learn
about yourself.

06:38.666 --> 06:40.568
Okay, terrific.

06:42.636 --> 06:44.572
Are you sure?

06:44.605 --> 06:45.639
Because the last time
I talked to you,

06:45.673 --> 06:47.808
you wanted to marry Jorge.

07:06.827 --> 07:08.662
Yeah, it's a great feeling.

07:08.696 --> 07:10.764
I didn't hear
you come in.

07:10.798 --> 07:12.500
So how's Mateo?

07:12.533 --> 07:14.201
Really nervous.

07:14.234 --> 07:15.035
How are you?

07:15.068 --> 07:18.806
Maybe we should talk
about us later.

07:18.839 --> 07:20.708
I meant about Mateo.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.576
And that lying
about the address thing.

07:22.610 --> 07:24.177
Oh.  Sorry.

07:24.211 --> 07:25.746
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
To remind you,

07:25.779 --> 07:27.715
they'd enrolled
in a great public kindergarten

07:27.748 --> 07:29.583
using Ro and Xo's address.

07:29.617 --> 07:31.151
I'm prepared, obviously.

07:31.184 --> 07:33.220
This is the place where we'd get
coffee every morning

07:33.253 --> 07:35.088
if we did, in fact,
live in the area.

07:35.122 --> 07:37.190
And I'm going
to run to my mom's

07:37.224 --> 07:39.860
and drop off toys in case
school officials ever come by.

07:39.893 --> 07:40.761
You dropped off toys
last week

07:40.794 --> 07:42.830
when you set up a room
for Mateo upstairs.

07:42.863 --> 07:44.998
I know, pay attention,
that's just what I told Rafael.

07:45.032 --> 07:45.999
Why?

07:46.033 --> 07:47.768
Because...

07:47.801 --> 07:49.537
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Come on, say it already!

07:49.570 --> 07:51.004
Last night...

07:51.038 --> 07:53.206
he kissed me.
What?

07:53.240 --> 07:54.542
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
I know!

07:54.575 --> 07:55.475
Completely out of
the blue.

07:55.509 --> 07:56.877
Well, not completely.
Couple months ago,

07:56.910 --> 07:58.746
you tried to get
in the shower with him.

07:58.779 --> 07:59.747
Exactly.

07:59.780 --> 08:00.948
Months ago.

08:00.981 --> 08:02.883
I mean, we're in
a different place now.

08:02.916 --> 08:06.720
Come on.
How was the kiss?

08:08.188 --> 08:09.557
I kissed Jane last night.

08:10.791 --> 08:12.192
And, Alba, it was...

08:12.225 --> 08:14.695
Not good.
What?

08:14.728 --> 08:15.829
I don't understand.

08:15.863 --> 08:17.531
You've had great kisses
before with him.

08:17.565 --> 08:19.567
I know. Next level.

08:19.600 --> 08:21.835
And I tried, honestly,
I gave it my all.

08:21.869 --> 08:23.804
I don't know,

08:23.837 --> 08:24.872
it-it just felt...

08:24.905 --> 08:27.007
Exactly the same.

08:27.040 --> 08:29.743
...completely different.
And the timing?

08:29.777 --> 08:32.713
I just had my heart broken.
What was he even thinking?

08:32.746 --> 08:36.584
And all I could think was,
"Finally. Finally."

08:36.617 --> 08:40.053
It felt like coming home.

08:40.087 --> 08:41.589
I don't even want to go home.

08:41.622 --> 08:42.956
You have to.

08:42.990 --> 08:45.826
I know, I know.

08:45.859 --> 08:48.829
I'll just...

08:48.862 --> 08:50.297
nip this whole thing in the bud.

08:50.330 --> 08:52.933
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Hey, that actually works.

09:06.179 --> 09:07.715
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Ah, yes. Where were we?

09:07.748 --> 09:09.182
You look like you need
a big kiss.

09:09.216 --> 09:12.886
Ah... mwah.

09:12.920 --> 09:14.087
You're gonna love kindergarten.

09:14.121 --> 09:15.756
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Debatable.
Now.

09:15.789 --> 09:16.957
One last time,
what is your name?

09:16.990 --> 09:19.793
Mateo Gloriano Rogelio
Solano Villanueva.

09:19.827 --> 09:20.794
Good.

09:20.828 --> 09:22.963
And what's your address?

09:22.996 --> 09:25.899
1312 Mockingbird Terrace.

09:25.933 --> 09:26.734
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
To be clear,

09:26.767 --> 09:29.036
that was Xo and Ro's address.
Perfect.

09:29.069 --> 09:30.938
And we need that
last piece of mail.

09:30.971 --> 09:33.006
Here it is.
Thank you so much.

09:33.040 --> 09:34.908
So many people try
to get into this district,

09:34.942 --> 09:36.309
we need to be really careful.

09:37.344 --> 09:38.846
Only our taxpayers.

09:45.653 --> 09:46.654
RAFAEL:
Jane.

09:52.159 --> 09:53.661
JANE :
I can't believe

09:53.694 --> 09:55.996
he's starting
kindergarten.

09:56.029 --> 09:57.397
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
I know.

09:57.430 --> 10:00.167
I remember when he was just
a syringe on a tray,

10:00.200 --> 10:02.035
waiting to be inserted
into the wrong woman.

10:02.069 --> 10:04.137
I know.

10:06.139 --> 10:08.776
Oh, you okay?
No.

10:08.809 --> 10:09.677
But I told myself

10:09.710 --> 10:11.111
I can't get emotional
until tomorrow.

10:11.144 --> 10:12.312
It's just registration.

10:12.345 --> 10:15.015
Kindergarten
is a big deal.

10:15.048 --> 10:17.250
Come on.

10:17.284 --> 10:19.853
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Wait. Is this a normal hug?

10:19.887 --> 10:21.789
Or is it weird
because of the kiss?

10:25.158 --> 10:27.160
Okay, I got to go
pick up the twins.
Mm-hmm.

10:27.194 --> 10:29.296
Uh, I will see you at home,
and we'll talk

10:29.329 --> 10:31.732
about... last night?

10:31.765 --> 10:33.867
Yes, good.

10:33.901 --> 10:36.870
Actually, maybe kiss first
and then talk.

10:36.904 --> 10:38.338
I'm sorry, I know we have
a lot to discuss,

10:38.371 --> 10:40.974
but, uh...

10:41.008 --> 10:42.810
...that was some kiss, huh?

10:42.843 --> 10:44.277
Yes, it-it was.

10:44.311 --> 10:46.814
XIOMARA:
I was shocked

10:46.847 --> 10:48.816
that any part of Rogelio,
no matter how small,

10:48.849 --> 10:50.150
suspected I was pregnant

10:50.183 --> 10:51.885
all those years ago.

10:51.919 --> 10:53.887
And I want to be able
to let go of it.

10:53.921 --> 10:56.189
Rogelio, how do you feel
about what Xiomara said?

10:56.223 --> 10:58.391
Hmm?

10:58.425 --> 11:03.230
Oh, well, um, I agree
on-on some level.

11:03.263 --> 11:07.701
But on another
level, I don't.

11:09.770 --> 11:11.939
You weren't
even listening.

11:11.972 --> 11:14.174
Of course I was.

11:14.207 --> 11:16.109
You've
been tweeting?

11:16.143 --> 11:18.078
No!

11:18.111 --> 11:20.113
Just one little tweet.

11:30.523 --> 11:32.059
I don't believe this.

11:32.092 --> 11:33.761
I am expected to
constantly tweet.

11:33.794 --> 11:36.329
I'm a tastemaker,
a 280 ambassador.

11:36.363 --> 11:38.265
But you know how important
this is to me.
You have no idea

11:38.298 --> 11:39.933
what an honor it was
And I don't need to hear

11:39.967 --> 11:41.969
to get 280 early.
any more about how
you got 280 early.

11:42.002 --> 11:43.136
It's important to me!

11:43.170 --> 11:44.237
Okay, okay.
XIOMARA:
Oh, my God.

11:44.271 --> 11:46.039
I'm gonna break that phone.

11:46.073 --> 11:48.108
I would like to see
you try.
Rogelio.

11:48.141 --> 11:50.443
Why are you reluctant
to discuss the past?

11:50.477 --> 11:53.246
Because he used
to be a Scientologist,

11:53.280 --> 11:54.848
so he doesn't
believe in therapy.

11:54.882 --> 11:56.817
That is not true.
Leah Remini and I

11:56.850 --> 11:58.418
totally changed our
minds about that.

11:58.451 --> 12:00.520
It's because we already
talked about what happened.

12:00.553 --> 12:02.322
THERAPIST:
So, l-let's not talk

12:02.355 --> 12:04.257
about your past with Xiomara.

12:04.291 --> 12:06.059
Let's talk
about your deeper past.

12:06.093 --> 12:08.495
Oftentimes, by understanding
the relationship

12:08.528 --> 12:11.098
with the formative female
in your life, your mother,

12:11.131 --> 12:13.767
it can help you understand
your relationship

12:13.801 --> 12:15.268
with the women
in your life now.

12:15.302 --> 12:17.137
My mother is an incredible
woman; she's perfect.

12:17.170 --> 12:19.172
She's strong, caring,

12:19.206 --> 12:22.075
kind, an amazing momager.

12:22.109 --> 12:23.543
Wait, what's a momager?

12:23.576 --> 12:26.213
My mother was my manager
as a child.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.248
So, when you say your line,

12:28.281 --> 12:34.287
show them your beautiful soul
and your beautiful teeth.

12:34.321 --> 12:36.223
THERAPIST: Having a business
relationship with the woman

12:36.256 --> 12:39.059
who's supposed to be loving you
unconditionally.

12:39.092 --> 12:41.561
All that pressure
and responsibility

12:41.594 --> 12:44.464
on such a little boy's
shoulders.

12:44.497 --> 12:46.299
How did that
make you feel?

12:46.333 --> 12:48.401
Well...

12:48.435 --> 12:52.439
yeah, it could sometimes
be hard.

12:54.241 --> 12:57.544
I mean, I had to support
my whole family.

12:57.577 --> 12:59.146
If I failed,

12:59.179 --> 13:02.983
my whole family
would suffer,

13:03.016 --> 13:05.886
which is just a lot

13:05.919 --> 13:09.156
f-for a little kid to handle.

13:09.189 --> 13:10.457
PETRA:
Oh, please, spare me.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.092
You did this to
get under my skin.

13:12.125 --> 13:13.260
I didn't.

13:13.293 --> 13:14.928
She came
highly recommended.

13:14.962 --> 13:16.029
Her name just
happened to be...

13:16.063 --> 13:18.832
Jane.

13:18.866 --> 13:20.367
And you are Petra?
Yes.

13:20.400 --> 13:21.935
And I really don't
need a lawyer.

13:25.072 --> 13:27.875
Then why am I here?

13:27.908 --> 13:29.943
My children's father felt
I should hire someone.

13:29.977 --> 13:32.279
Because you were the only person
at the scene of the murder?

